                          <div class="blog-hover-color"></div>
                          <h4 class="alt-font post-title font-weight-600 text-white display-block margin-5px-bottom">Center Honors Beverly Daniel Tatum, Celebrates 20th Book Anniversary</h4>
                          <div class="author">
                              <span class="text-white text-uppercase text-extra-small display-inline-block alt-font-3">February 2018</span>
                          </div>
                          <div class="separator-line-horrizontal-full bg-medium-gray margin-seven-tb md-margin-four-tb"></div>
                          <p class="text-white">In 1997, clinical psychologist Beverly Daniel Tatum published, “Why Are All the Black Kids Sitting Together in the Cafeteria? And Other Conversations About Race.” Educators, graduate students, and appreciators of this seminal book gathered on the USC campus to applaud Tatum and to celebrate the publication of the 20th anniversary edition of her important text.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
              </li>
              <!-- end post item -->
              <!-- start post item -->
