                          <a href="blog-post-layout-01.html">
                            <%= image_tag("https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BEO3H5BOlFk/maxresdefault.jpg")%>
                          </a>
                          <div class="blog-categories bg-white text-black text-uppercase text-extra-small alt-font-3">news</div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="post-details padding-30px-all bg-red sm-padding-20px-all">
                          <div class="blog-hover-color"></div>
                          <h4 class="alt-font post-title font-weight-600 text-white display-block margin-5px-bottom">Stokes Releases “Dear White Counselor” and “Black Bruins” Follow Up</h4>
                          <div class="author">
                              <span class="text-white text-uppercase text-extra-small display-inline-block alt-font-3">January 2018</span>
                          </div>
                          <div class="separator-line-horrizontal-full bg-medium-gray margin-seven-tb md-margin-four-tb"></div>
                          <p class="text-white">Sy Stokes made national news in November 2013 for “The Black Bruins,” his groundbreaking spoken word video that has since been viewed over 2.3 million times on YouTube. The video featured him and several other Black undergraduate men who presented a range of shocking statistics regarding myriad racial inequities at UCLA. Stokes’ poem also illuminated several other institutionalized barriers to success for him and other Black male students at his then undergraduate institution.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
              </li>
              <!-- end post item -->
              <!-- start post item -->
              <li class="grid-item wow fadeInUp last-paragraph-no-margin">
