                          <h4 class="alt-font post-title font-weight-600 text-white display-block margin-5px-bottom">Grant to Fund Protest Policy Research</h4>
                          <div class="author">
                              <span class="text-white text-uppercase text-extra-small display-inline-block alt-font-3">December 2017</span>
                          </div>
                          <div class="separator-line-horrizontal-full bg-medium-gray margin-seven-tb md-margin-four-tb"></div>
                          <p class="text-white">The National Center for Institutional Diversity at the University of Michigan recently awarded Charles Davis a grant to examine state and institutional policies. “The Campus Protest Policy Project” will critically analyze policies aimed at punishing students engaged in campus protests, particularly those directly resisting hate speech at their colleges and universities.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
              </li>
