                          <div class="author">
                              <span class="text-white text-uppercase text-extra-small display-inline-block alt-font-3">September 2017</span>
                          </div>
                          <div class="separator-line-horrizontal-full bg-medium-gray margin-seven-tb md-margin-four-tb"></div>
                          <p class="text-white">As part of our RISE for Boys and Men of Color project, the Center hosted a two-day convening on the USC campus that brought together researchers from education, health, criminal justice, workforce development, social policy, and human services. Scholars came from all over the United States. Also, several professionals from community-based and youth-serving organizations in Los Angeles attended. USC Sociology Professor Manuel Pastor, one of the Center’s faculty affiliates, was a keynote speaker. </p>
